89
00:21:25.998 --> 00:21:43.047
Incoming livestream: Yeah, I think… so, specifically, we used the offline accuracy one, where it was, you know, before the threat model or changes to the threat model agent were released, we would base off of that. In the next iteration, and this is something we're trying to build out, is to give more online

90
00:21:43.048 --> 00:22:00.487
Incoming livestream: evaluation, right? So when a threat model is done on a new security review, how would it perform? And the way we're thinking of approaching this is, you know, traditionally, if it's a human, sort of, you know, grading it, that's great and all, but that involves, like, more security process, like, you would need all the humans to do it,

91
00:22:00.487 --> 00:22:09.237
Incoming livestream: And that's not always guaranteed. So what we're trying to integrate is to have our security, threat model tool that we mentioned earlier as sort of the source of truth.

92
00:22:09.237 --> 00:22:25.388
Incoming livestream: And our threat model agent would generate, hey, these are the threats that we found, and users would use that as a source of truth to click approve, sort of deny, and utilize those metrics to give more of an online-like feedback loop, and that would provide more accuracy.

93
00:22:25.387 --> 00:22:28.287
Incoming livestream: So, we're looking at, you know, from both approaches.

